  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "Creating an effective Pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3 involves focusing on several key attributes to maximize your damage output and versatility. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the primary stats you should consider when building your Pyromancer:\n\n### Key Stats:\n\n1. **Intelligence (INT)**: \n   - This stat increases the power of your sorceries and is vital for scaling damage with certain pyromancies, particularly those that deal magic damage. Aim for at least **30-40 INT** for better scaling.\n\n2. **Faith (FTH)**: \n   - Faith affects the power of certain pyromancies and is crucial if you want to utilize pyromancies that scale with Faith. Aiming for around **20-30 FTH** allows you to use many of the more powerful pyromancies effectively.\n\n3. **Attunement (ATT)**: \n   - This stat determines the number of spell slots you have. You\u2019ll want to invest in Attunement to have enough slots for your desired pyromancies. Aim for around **16-20 ATT** to get a good number of slots.\n\n4. **Endurance (END)**: \n   - Endurance increases your stamina and equip load, which is crucial for maintaining a good balance between rolling and casting. Around **20-30 END** is typically recommended.\n\n5. **Vigor (VIG)**: \n   - Vigor increases your health. Having a decent health pool is important, especially in PvE. Aim for **25-30 VIG** to survive tougher encounters.\n\n6. **Strength (STR) and Dexterity (DEX)**: \n   - While not the primary focus for a Pyromancer, you may want to invest in these stats if you wish to use specific weapons effectively. Typically, keeping them low (around **10-16**) is sufficient unless you want to use certain melee weapons.\n\n### Suggested Build Overview:\n\n- **Vigor**: 25-30\n- **Attunement**: 16-20\n- **Endurance**: 20-30\n- **Intelligence**: 30-40\n- **Faith**: 20-30\n- **Strength**: 10-16\n- **Dexterity**: 10-16\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Equipment**: Equip the **Pyromancer's Flame** or **Ishma's Flame** for your casting. Look for armor that provides good poise without making you too heavy.\n  \n- **Rings**: Consider the **Great Swamp Ring** (boosts pyromancy damage), **Bellowing Dragoncrest Ring** (boosts sorcery damage), and **Cloranthy Ring** (boosts stamina recovery) for optimal performance.\n\n- **Pyromancies**: Focus on powerful pyromancies like **Great Chaos Fire Orb**, **Fire Storm**, and **Black Flame** for high damage output.\n\n- **Strategy**: Mix ranged pyromancy attacks with melee combat. Use your pyromancies to deal damage from a distance, and switch to melee when enemies close in.\n\nBy balancing these attributes and focusing on your spell choices, you\u2019ll create a powerful Pyromancer build that can tackle the challenges of Dark Souls 3 effectively! Happy burning!",
